<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0048266> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Any process that results in a change in the behavior of an organism as a result of a pain stimulus. Pain stimuli cause activation of nociceptors, peripheral receptors for pain, include receptors which are sensitive to painful mechanical stimuli, extreme heat or cold, and chemical stimuli." .
