_:Bbbfff54f2a7f179f3ebe6bbe5ec21dfe <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "in FMA, tendon is an organ component that with parts dense-irregular-connective-tissue of tendon and dense-irregular-connective-tissue of tendon sheath; we follow VSAO in making it a subtype of the former. In VSAO tendons connect muscle to bone; in WP the def states integument (e.g. auricular muscles) - but JB confirms this is not actually tendon but aponeurosis" .
